adviseScripts.text: I fully understand that I need to wear a mask to control my power but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But, sometimes, it's quite suffocating.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: You can secretly take it off sometimes.
Even so, it can be helpful at times.
I can't do... that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: If my boss finds out I take it off, she'll get mad at me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I can see that you're disappointed, but there is nothing I can do. I'm sorry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: You're right. It's a contradiction.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: When I go on missions with Guillotine,
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: It feels better hiding behind this mask.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Maiden's worries.
I... have a big problem.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: When a certain someone treats me nicely, even just a little bit, I get butterflies in my stomach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I just don't know what to do with myself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Give a pat on the shoulder as a sign of support.
You need to see them for who they really are.
*Thump*
See?! My heart skipped a beat!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Do you mean if I got to know their quirks, then, perhaps I wouldn't like them anymore?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But, no matter how I look at it...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: ... I just can't see anything wrong with you, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Maiden's concerns about falling in love.
Master of the Kotodama.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Judge of the blood-red rose.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: These are some of the ridiculous nicknames given to me by Guillotine on SNS.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Can you tell Guillotine to stop it? I'm dying of embarrassment over here!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Have patience. This is a burden you must learn to bear.
I will talk to Guillotine.
Commander...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: You and Guillotine are both so weird.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: W-will you? Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Thank you! You don't know how depressed I was until now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Maiden talk about her relationships.
Sometimes, I hear Nikkes talk about Guillotine and me like we're urban legends or something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: They say that if they become Irregulars, the Grim reaper will come and take them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I don't know what to do with these rumors.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: That is difficult.
Don't worry. Just be you.
Right? I don't think there is an answer to this problem.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Still, I feel so much better after talking to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I always try my best to do that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: ... It's not that easy, though, no matter how hard I try.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I have a deep conversation with Maiden about her fate.
Look at my clothes!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: What do you think? How do I look?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: It looks heavy.
It suits you.
You saw right through me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: ... Th-thank you. I never thought I would hear a compliment.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Maiden about her look.
I wish I had a friend who I could share my thoughts with.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Someone normal, you know? Not like Guillotine the weirdo.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I can introduce you to some other Nikkes if you like.
Am I not enough?
Mmmm... Thank you for the offer...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But I try to avoid making friends with Nikkes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I might have to kill them with my own hands later on. You never know.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I don't think I'll be able to do that if they're my friends.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: That's not true!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I think you're a dear friend. I don't really deserve you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I spend some meaningful time with Maiden.
C-Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Do you notice anything different about me today?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Hmmm... The rose in your hair seems fresher.
Something different?
Huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But this is... an artificial flower.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: That's not it. It's...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I stayed up late last night, and my eyebags have worsened.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I'm glad you didn't notice it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I have a short talk with Maiden who, I think, tested me a little.
What do you think about the boss, Ingrid?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Well, even myself, I find her quite scary. But I just wanted to know what others think of her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I'm also afraid of Ingrid.
She's kinder than you think.
R-right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I feel somewhat reassured since I'm not the only one feeling this way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: ... That may be true...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: people can be both kind and scary at the same time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Maiden about Ingrid.
Commander, do you have some time to spare tomorrow?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I know you always have a hectic schedule, but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I have some commitments tomorrow.
I can take some time off in the evening.
Right. Of course.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I guess that's the bitter reality, then.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: R-really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I didn't expect that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Good thing I didn't give up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Maiden.
What do you do when you're uncomfortable with one of your squad members?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: No, wait, I should tell you the whole truth.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Every time Guillotine uses her powers and shouts, "Dragon of the Deep!", I feel so embarrassed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Just pretend you don't know her.
Yell something even darker and more cringy.
I already tried that...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But since we're wearing the same uniform, it's obvious we're on the same team.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: No one ever falls for it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Y-you're not kidding?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Maiden about her squad members.
Sigh... I really want to lie down.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: After we're done here, can I chill in your room for a bit?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Sure.
Ingrid asked me to send you back as soon as this is over.
Thanks! I thought you were going to refuse me point-blank.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: It'll be our little secret from the boss.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Sigh... I thought you'd stand up for me...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Oh well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I proceeded to have a lovely conversation.
Commander, do you think I'm weird?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: After all, I'm a Nikke who executes other Nikkes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Sounds perfectly normal to me.
It is a bit out of the ordinary.
N-normal?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: That's the first time I've ever heard someone say that...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: So in your eyes, I'm just like any other Nikke?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: ... Thank you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I'm glad you're not too weirded out by it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Most people go on about how unique my job is, but they all
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: keep their distance in the end.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But not you, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I have a meaningful discussion.
Commander, what kind of music do you usually listen to?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Pulse-pounding music that gets the blood pumping.
Slow and serene music.
Hmmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: That's what Guillotine listens to as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: It's perfect for using as an alarm.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Seems you and I have the same taste in music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I listen to quiet music, it helps me sleep better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Do you like to listen to music before you go to bed?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: During our discussion, Maiden and I decided to put on some music.
What things of a person you would have a crush on?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I mean like personality, appearance, etc.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: The voice of a beautiful lady hidden under a face mask.
The sharp eyes hidden under an eye mask.
M-mask and beautiful lady...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Are you talking about me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: It reminds me of someone.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: ... Should I also use an eye mask from now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I have a debate with Maiden about the attraction of a person.
Argh, I hate wearing a face mask! It's such a pain eating out with it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: There has to be a better solution...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Take your mask off when there is no one around, then eat.
Don't eat out as often.
That's what I've been doing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: What else can I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Hmmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I'll try, but it's so depressing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Because of this mask, I have to restrain myself from eating too much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I try to come up with a mask that would allow you to eat at the same time.
I think our squad is being given way too many assignments.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: If we're not on the surface fighting Raptures,
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: we're in the Ark going up against Irregulars.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: We never have a moment's respite.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Ask for a raise.
I'll make a request for you to be taken off this mission.
I think that's a good idea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden takes out her phone and is about to call Ingrid...
But the boss is really intimidating.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Umm... Can you call her for me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I don't want that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Then I won't have as many opportunities to run into you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: All I'm asking for is something simple, like a 20% raise.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I talk about the working conditions over at Extrinsic during our discussion.
I've been dying to get this limited edition handbag.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: They just released it,
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: but I already spent too much money this month...what should I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Dip into next month's allowance.
Start working part-time jobs.
But...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: There are more limited edition handbags I want next month...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: That's an amazing idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I can work for you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: We can even discuss the terms of my employment during our discussions. I'm sure we'll be able to come to an agreement.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I have a conversation about borrowing money.
When it's just me by myself at night, I get lonely.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Commander, what would you do in a situation like this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I would call my friends.
I would enjoy some alone time.
Is it okay to do that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I always kept myself from doing that because I thought I'd be disturbing everyone else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But since you said it's okay, I'll go ahead and hit them up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: You sound just like Guillotine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Please, I'm begging you, don't turn into a second Guillotine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I have a conversation on how to get over loneliness.
Online games are so fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: You feel like you belong. You can talk to all these people you might normally have a difficult time talking to in real life.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: But on the other hand, I feel all this pressure to try and change my schedule to accommodate them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: What am I supposed to do here?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Play a single-player game.
Arrange a gathering them after midnight.
Are you even listening to me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I don't want to stop playing online games.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Hey, that's right! Most people aren't working after midnight.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: I'll bring it up in the group chat and see what they think. Thanks, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden and I talk about the life of a gamer.
All of the Extrinsic Squad's operations are classified, so I can't confide in anyone about anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: People end up thinking I just sit around all day and horse around.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: It really upsets me, but what can I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Well, isn't there some truth to it?
I understand what you all do, and have nothing but respect for you.
Hey!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: You're supposed to be looking after my mental wellbeing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: There's no harm in telling me a white lie every once in a while...
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden wiped away her tears.
You're the only person who understands my predicament.
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Have I ever told you how much I love you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Maiden

adviseScripts.text: Maiden shared more of her troubles with me during our discussion.
